caption: We had a great experience.   This is a great local gem. This place has a lot of room to spread out and keep your social distance.  We had the fresh homemade personal pizzas.  We recommend The Goat and the BLT Pizza.  The Strawberry Walnut salad is a delight for your senses!  It is also big enough to share.   Service was attentive but not hovering.
We love Trattoria 225! Their entrees and pizza are fabulous, not to mention their customer service. Always an absolute treat!
Food, drinks and service are great!
Great food at a reasonable price
We always enjoyed dining at this restaurant in the past, and now are enjoying takeout from them. We think it's the best pizza around.
Amazing food all around, must try if you are in the area. Love this place
I just had the wise guy pizza and it was super 😋! And the Caesar salad was interestingly good too!!! Thank you guys!!!
Used them to cater dinner to Hines hospital for 70 vets for Thanksgiving the vet's love the food will use them again also when they open again will go there to eat
Went there for cocktails. One of the best bartenders around

Local OP gem. We had a party of 12 for a wedding rehearsal and tried a few dishes. The gnocchi was absolutely delicious as were the pizzas. We could not have asked for better service or a better ambience for our event.
(Translated by Google) I was fascinated 😉  (Original) Quede fascinada 😉
Great place for make your own gourmet pizza!
The pizza is very good and the exterior looks amazing and cozy at night. They have very cool artwork throughout the restaurant. Highly recommended.

We ordered their 2 for 20 in 2 different occasions . The first time we ordered 2 pizzas and  picked up as told in 15 min. The pizzas were hot and delicious. Today I do the same. I pick up in 15 min as instructed and the pizzas are lukewarm and look and taste as if they had been made long in advance. If the pizzas were made within this 15 time minute frame that should have been impossible. This is supposed to be a quality establishment. I expect the pizza to be made to order. It shows little respect to the customers, thinking that they will not notice and to the food, ruining quality ingredients. I will give this place one more chance and update this review as needed.

So dissatisfied. I ordered 2 pizzas to go and was told 15 minutes. I picked up on time. The pizzas taste like they were made ahead. HOURS ahead. I so seldom order out during this pandemic. I feel like I was robbed.
Excellent place, food was great, service is excellent, Thursday the have 2 pizzas for $20, beer on tap is really good as well.
The waiters were super attentive.Services are awesome.Highly recommended.
Wonderful desert tonight..Felt very comfortable to me..
Great service and excellent food but only offering a limited menu because of the Wuhan virus. The pizzas are excellent!!
First time back since the current events and had a wonderful dinner and experience

Interesting how you keep posting about businesses closing. I have been to your restaurant MANY times in the last eight years and have had the WORST experience from the owner and his daughter (a storm was coming and you were more worried about you plastic furniture outside than my wife and I celebrating our anniversary). I confronted you about it and you didn’t seem to care about the loss of business, you said “if you don’t like it, don’t come” Then 2 days later I see you cruising around on your Harley Davidson. Maybe you just post in jest of being on the chopping block yourself?
I had an excellent time at this restaurant. We enjoyed the extraordinary vibes and the food. The waiters were super attentive. I’m content we finally decided to visit here.
No accommodation for special needs families.
Phenomenal food, great atmosphere, and warm and wonderful service from Savannah.  What a great place!
Excellent food and great ambiance at this local Oak Park haunt....
Food was not as expected but a pleasant surprise.
Lovely and kid friendly.
Family favorite!

Have been to Trattoria for salad, pizza or pasta dishes and they have all been great. Family lives within walking distance and we go every time we visit. Staff is great and especially good with young children.
Friendly staff and delicious food, I now know where my future date night will take place.
Great food and great service.  Couldn't ask for anything more.

Went there in summer and had a wonderful mussels dish. Yesterday I went again, the ravioli entree was very good but a small portion.  Caesar dressing was not good. They give you a plate of olive oil for your bread and getting a bus boy to get me more was impossible! Creme brûlée was the worst I’ve ever had! And I was charged for someone else’s bottle of wine. No ‘sorry’. Just- I wondered where that went- glad you found it. I’ll think twice about going back- and I’ll double check my bill!!!!
Been here several time for work dinners. The food is always excellent, the service is great as well.  Definitely worth giving it a go.
An amazing place to dine! Magnificent food, impeccable service. Always a the best!
Good food....great service
Tried this spot in the past with my friend and I am hooked since then. I liked the great atmosphere and flavorful dishes and drinks. Highly recommended.

I had a grilled chicken Caesar salad to go. Never had a grilled salad before but this was delicious, it had a smoky flavor and the lettuce was still firm the homemade creamy Caesar dressing was terrific. This place is located in the art district of Oak Park, which is really become a great area in Oak Park.I also picked up some Portobello ravioli for my son, which he devoured. How do you recommend this place to try. Although I didn't stay the venue on inside is beautiful and spacious
Had a awesome experience in this place with my daughter. The food comes out quickly and the service is just fantastic. Prices are affordable.
Our go to Italian restaurant in OP.  Great for kids and Tuesday pizza special is awesome!
Wonderful food! Nice variety & excellent service!! It has become a family tradition when we are in Oak Park
Wonderful pizza and freshly made pasta!
The ambiance is really nice & the foot is amaze-balls!

I haven't even eaten my food but I place a carry out order Spaghetti Carbonara  and wanted to have a drink at the bar and wait. Now there is visible seats at the bar but I'm told to stop and wait because there isn't any space. I'm confused because I see at least 3 open seats. The greeter advised me that the bartender was really busy so I couldn't sit. Luckily my food was already ready and I was able to pay as I'm doing so 3 ladies white of course are leaving the bar. So needless to say my first impression is that this is clearly a racist establishment and prefers certain customers. Just disgusting and disappointing and as I write this I should have left my order to there. LESSON LEARNED
Need more vegetarian options. Noisy
Delicious gluten free options! Make sure to request a gf roll and order dessert.
Great food, spacious rooms.
(Translated by Google) Perefeto  (Original) Perefeto
Food is excellent!   I can't eat dairy so they made special dish,grilled  chicken & roasted potatoes. Really enjoyed my meal!
My new favorite Italian restaurant in Oak Park , Caesar salad, mussels and pizza delicious. Most of all everything was very fresh !!! Love this place !
Great place
Very good pasta. My favorite is a creamy mushroom pasta with chicken. We have been here twice for 2 small events(bridal& baby shower) plenty of food served.
Good neighborhood spot
Should expand menu
Love Dave..
Very warm and comfortable atmosphere. Everything we ordered was perfect, from the appetizers to desert. The service was amazing! I will return regularly for my Italian food fix!
Great wood-fired pizza and nice beer list.
Grate authentic italian food with grate service and drinks (Dave the bartender is one of the nicest and most professional people you will ever meet)
Great dining experience.

I've been here several times over the last few years for company dinners and the staff here are absolutely amazing. They treat us like family and have since our very first visit. The food is phenomenal, especially the bruschetta and pizza.
Stopped in to place a carry out order. Very nice ambiance and staff. Menu selection looks good.
Lovely family restaurant. Monday night's kids eat free.

Great family friendly Italian restaurant. Their pizza is really very good. They offer good gluten free pizza as well. The child menu portion is very small, not appropriate for bigger kids over three years old. Salads are really good, enjoy the beet salad! The three creme brulee, tiramisu and gelato are treats.
Great food. Excellent bar.
Local gem. Good food. Good staff. Upscale but casual.

This restaurant had a very nice atmosphere and we're welcoming to casual or more dressier groups. The food was really good and the service was great. It is a nice gem and it makes me want to visit the south half of Oak Park more. I will be back.

Food was very good. The short rib ravioli was especially lovely. Food came quickly. Atmosphere is lovely. Part of our wait staff was a little standoffish, at one point he came over and just stood there... He was waiting for our order, but it was weird, he didn't say "have you decided" or "what can I get for you?" Just stood there.
Comfortable neighborhood place, moderately priced. Nothing flashy or spectacular, just a place to come to regularly for good food with friends.

Trattoria 225 is a hidden secret gem of a restaurant on Harrison Street in the Art District of Oak Park. The food is consistently perfect. The service is the same. Every time I leave this place I ask myself why isn't the restaurant packed. I think anyone who likes Italian food would appreciate this restaurant.
Good Italian but pricey
Great food and service.
Little pricey considering the quality.

I was walking by the place and stopped in. I asked the hostess if they had pizza. She said that they did and gave me a menu. I was originally going to just get takeout but then asked the hostess if I could eat at a table. She said I could sit at the bar which I did. The hostess brought the pizza to me at the bar and I paid her and gave her an approximately 40% gratuity. Because I did not order the pizza through him, the bartender, however, did not want to be bothered with me. I had to repeatedly ask him for water which I should not of had to do. If a water glass is empty, good service staff fill it with more water automatically but not this guy. The third time I asked him for more water I watched him serve all of the other people at the bar, get the servers their drinks and then talk a few minutes with the two other bar patrons before re-filling my water. He did not want to wait on someone else's customer who was only drinking water. I left the place thirsty because I did not want to go through that whole ordeal just for a glass of water.  On my way out, I talked to the manager. He agreed with me and said that he would have a talk with the bartender. But he did not appear to care. I told him that I was leaving his establishment thirsty because I did not want to go through the whole ordeal of getting another glass of water with my meal. A caring manager would have went and got his thirsty customer a glass of water but not this manager. I told the manager the whole story and that I regretted even setting foot in his restaurant. He did not even offer an apology. Never again!
Great menu, quick service, and kid-friendly. Will definitely be back.
It’s awesome!!!!!
Very comfortable and friendly neighborhood Italian restaurant. Excellent salads, appetizers and pizza. Entrees are not as consistently great, but still a very good value.
Excellent food and service
The place is nice and the price is good too
Adorable place. We went for a rehearsal dinner. great food. Great atmosphere.

Go here a lot for date night. They have good food and great desserts. Also a good cocktail selection. The service is always great and the atmosphere is quiet enough for conversation but loud enough to know you are out on the town. The table spacing is perfect.
Always on point. Salmon is my favorite, but the pizzas are perfect.  My neighborhood favorite.
Best bartenders (with best stories and cutest kids) on Harrison.
Great atmosphere and food. Wait staff was very good
Very warm and comfortable atmosphere. Everything my wife and I ordered was perfect, from the appetizers to desert. The service was amazing! I will return regularly for my Italian food fix!
The shrimp scampi was yummy!

I went there on Super Bowl Sunday with my sister and had the best martini and the best customer service. The bartender knew the menu inside and out and was courteous and generous with his time. He was able to describe the wine bar menu and was able to distinctively suggest wines that were spot on. Imagine my surprise when I actually liked the US wines that he recommended. The appetizers were really on point as well. I had the mussels and my sister had the shrimp with polenta . Both were really good, and great value with great customer service. Our  bartender’s name was Dave I believe.
Monday night kids eat free
Excellent chicken. Best meal I've had in awhile. Would invite anyone to check it out
Pizza is good.
Kids eat free on Mondays!

We love this place. Drinks are great and they offer wonderful wine selections plus craft brews. Food is always excellent and very creative. I never heard of a grilled watermelon salad (was a special and decilious) and the different menu offerings that the chef prepares.  Register to get email updates on their weekly specials which change every Friday. They have updated their regular menu too. Can't say enough about Bill and all the wonderful staff. It's a little gem on Harrison St in Oak Park!  Was just dining here tonight and we had a group of 7 for dinner. We live near by but the rest of our party drove from quite away. They all loved the food and said they would drive back again.  Great job Trattoria 225!
Very good place for all ages. Good menu selection.

Food was phenomenal. The mussels were tender and sauce had the perfect amount of lemon giving it a nice tang that was good enough it could be drank as soup. Chicken saltimbocca was fabulous --plenty of capers with a nice hint of brine in the sauce. Cool decor.

Nice restaurant, good food and good service! Lobster ravioli is tasty, so is the beef rib with risotto. Their pizzas also are better than I expected. They had very friendly and prompt service when we came in. I have never seen the restaurant completely filled so there  never seems to be a wait so you can expect to be seated quickly. Our food was prepared much faster than we expected.  The restaurant has a nice ambience and is the nicest restaurant in the Harrison Street Art District. We have also ordered pickup from them several times with no issues.
Our third visit over the last couple of years. Great food at a reasonable price. Nice art adorning the walls and windows.
Yummy pizza at Trattoria 225 tonight, including one with gluten free crust.
Food is very good and atmosphere is very low key and upscale at the same time - a hard balance to achieve.
Good dinner, service & atmosphere.
Always enjoyable. Great food and service for a fair price.
The boss is rude to his delivery drivers. Food is great though!
Delicious food! Its our place to go dor Mother's day  brunch

Food was great. Service wasn't bad...not stellar. I tipped 20% because that's my normal rate, but after we left I regretted it. I had asked for my son's spaghetti dinner to be boxed since he barely ate any of it. It was a massive portion...turns out we were given a remarkably tiny box to take home. It was glaringly obvious that they did not give us the portion we paid for and was leftover, they instead gave us "some" of what was left. Disappointing. My son was particularly disappointed.
Amazing food! Can't recommend it enough!

Ambiance was great.  Their ingredients were fresh but food lacked flavor. I ordered cioppino which was their special and it was salty for me. Bread was hard but it did taste good. Pizza was ok but for the price , I expected more. Gluten free meals are available which was why we went here to accommodate our 85 year old aunt with dietary restrictions.
Very cozy and good service, the food is outstanding.my favorite place in oak park
Very good food
Very nice place with soul and exelent service for a romantik diner or date

Our family group of 7 including 3 grandkids went here for dinner at my daughter's suggestion.   From the outside my expectations were not high.  However, inside this larger restaurant we found a great fun atmosphere.  The service was friendly and efficient and everyone, including the kids, was very happy with their meals.  Mine was exceptional.  Next time we visit Oak Park we will surely dine here again.
Lively place

While the food was terrific, the service absolutely ruined my mother's birthday celebration.  Our waitress was very rude and made faces and comments that turned everybody's positive experience into a negative one.  It was an extremely promising evening that was sent into an immediate downward spiral.  Be cautious.

My family and I went here recently while on vacation and ordered gluten-free pizzas. They were excellent even though the cost of the pizza is a little higher. I love small businesses like this one and if I ever come to Chicago again I will definitely come here again.
Spaghetti carbonara was great, service was excellent.  Excited to try more from this place, had a good atmosphere.
Great food, owner is super nice!  We had a private party here and it worked out great with custom pizzas and lots of drinks and other food.

This Place Is Simply HORRIBLE! My visit took place on 3/I9/2016, I ordered the Eggplant Lasagna and it tasted like a strong leather belt seasoned with olives! It took 3 different types of knives to cut through it, even harder to thoroughly bite through it and digest it. I immediately sent it back (wasn't charged) and in return I received Tilapia, which was basically a large burnt fish stick with tartar sauce! If you closed your eyes you would have no clue it was tilapia! I would not recommend. Oh, and the lemonade was dollar store powder packet quality, the nerve of them to put an actual lemon at the top, are you kidding me?! got my $$ back for that as well. the place looks awesome, very good ambiance, but the food, I wouldn't even give to a homeless cat.

I live in the neighborhood so I was excited to try this place. Boy did it disappoint. I ordered the pasta with the seafood in it and the pasta didn't taste fresh and homemade and the seafood tasted like it was from a bag of mixed frozen seafood. Something I could have made at home. This is the dish I order at every Italian restaurant and gauge the restaurant if they use fresh pasta and fresh seafood.

I have so much love for this place! It's so hard to find good Italian food since I already know how to make really good pizza and pasta.  Highly recommend the Duck Con Fit or chopped Italian salad or my favorite is "The Goat" pizza!! Not to mention their weekly seasonly specials they are always offering. Don't forget that they offer two for one pizza nights on Tuesdays!  Great location nestled in the heart of the Arts District in Oak Park. Tons of fabulous local artists display their work for free and I adore their bar area in case you just want a drink. I have brought several family members and friends here and they have all highly enjoyed their food. Hope you enjoy your food as much as I have!
Great place, quality food and delicious wood fired pizzas.
Everything is fantastic! The food, dining room, and staff are all top notch.
Was there for a large party with fixed menu. Food was all done very well, butternut squash ravioli was the highlight. Good service as well.

Tonight my wife and I had dinner at Trattoria 225 and the food was outstanding.  We had the Risotto and Bolognese.  Our server gave us separate plates so we could share both meals.  Service was great, only topped by the food.  Staff was friendly and even kidded around with me.  This is a great place if you are looking for a date night, or if you have kids and need a restaurant that kid friendly.  Can't wait to go back.
grilled romaine salad and flatbreads are memorable.servers are earnest if not really well trained. restaurant is noisy. good reliable neighborhood place.

I gave a 4 star based on what they are trying to do: use local produce. I had the orechette which had a great, bold spice to it. It was saltier than I like but I'm used to low salt. Wines were at a decent price and well poured. Nothing outstanding but drinkable. For dessert I had a disappointing "something chocolate" which was a chocolate bundt cake with vanilla gelato and chocolate and caramel sauces drizzle over. Not much chocolate flavor to the dry, cakey confection. I ordered a rye, Tempelton's, to go with it (I love the pairing of chocolate and bourbon). This was a more disappointing pour and I find Tempelton a thin rye, at best.. Next time, go for the Knob Creek with a side of water.  Altogether, a restaurant to keep my eye on and try again. It has potential. It can be real noisy with just a few people so plan accordingly.
